ğŸš€ Executive Summary

Enterprise-grade RPA solution that automates an end-to-end SAP GUI Sales Order & Material de-allocation process, replacing a repetitive daily manual task with a resilient, validated, and fault-tolerant automation.
The solution integrates Python business logic, SAP GUI scripting, validation checkpoints, retry mechanisms, and automated reporting, delivering ~50 business days saved per year and eliminating operational risk.

ğŸ¯ Business Problem

The de-allocation process was executed manually on a daily basis and suffered from:

High dependency on SAP session state

Repetitive and time-consuming execution

Risk of human error (wrong SOs or materials)

No validation of execution results

No visibility of time loss or efficiency impact

This generated inefficiency, rework, and risk in a productive SAP environment.

ğŸ§  Solution Overview

A modular and resilient RPA architecture was designed to fully automate the process while separating business logic from SAP interaction.
Each critical step includes validation checkpoints, controlled retries, and error handling to ensure safe execution in SAP GUI.

ğŸ–¼ RPA Orchestration Breakdown

High-level flow:

SAP session initialization and cleanup

Business logic preparation (Python)

Input file validation (SO & Material files)

SAP navigation with screen/state validation

De-allocation execution

Result validation (success / failure)

Controlled retry loop (if required)

Results extraction

Automated email notification

Safe SAP shutdown

